Hi Googly foodies! My best friend and I were in DC and we decided to ditch the hotel’s restaurant for a food adventure! I of course used my google map and got my eyes for this amazingly beautiful colorful restaurant called Nando’s PERi-PERi! In Connecticut Ave. In DC. Boy, I am so glad we went for this one. As we stood in line we were greeted by amazingly friendly hostess and she gave us a short explanation of the ordering process. A note to you all, their expertise are in hot, spicy chicken! So as someone that I appreciate my tastebuds and don’t want to harm them! I ordered 1/2 PERi-PERi chicken “plainish”==>meaning no hot species on my chicken! With the sides of corn on the cob and their amazing rice! Let me tell u foodies! OMG! My mouth had a party! First off the chicken was juicy, tasty and crispy all in one bite! Although I ordered the palinish but my chicken had very good specie to it. Not too hot not too bland! Just perfect! I have traveled all over in Europe and ate many chicken in my life but I can tell u all if you’re in DC area and in the mood for some delicious food! Make sure you check these guys out! In short, the food was so good that my friend had to order more for his dinner with family and did a take out from them. As for me... I loved the taste of the food and kind and warm atmosphere of the restaurant. If you are going there for the first time go for their 1/2 chicken with 2 sides! It is reasonable and u get a lot of food for what u pay. Thumbs up! I searched them and find out they do have a branch in my hometown! So I am so going to try them again at home! Awesome place to eat in or to do a take out! As always! Enjoy your dream food! Life is too short not to do it! GO.😂👍

This place has gone downhill since my last visit.  The place used to be great.  Now it's full of a staff that seemingly is more interested in talking amongst themselves than their jobs or serving customers. Examples: I asked to get additional salad dressing and got a visible eyeroll.  When I asked if there was any more bottles of the medium sauce, I first had to interrupt two staff members obviously casual conversation to do so,  then my response I got was the bottles were being cleaned.  Instead of offering some from the kitchen in a condiment container, they just went back to talking.  The tables are in need of serious cleaning.  I wiped up the water ring from my glass and got back a grey napkin where the moisture was.  This was true of the 2 tables next to me as well, i know, i repeated the experiment.  The tables also feel tacky to the touch.  Then there was the food itself.  I ordered butterfly chicken breast.  They usually come with a great grill chared skin and juicy chicken.  This time i got inedible skin that was rubbery and gross as well as chicken that was not any more edible, the salad greens were wilted and seemingly warm, almost like they sat under a heat lamp.  So overall I was pretty disappointed in my visit to say the least.  This is probably my favorite of chain restaurants,  so I hope there is a course correction back to the great place it once was and still could be.  Napkin picture attached for proof of claims on table cleanliness.  This was a fresh napkin used for one swipe of a water ring on the edge of the table.

The worse Nando's I've ever visited.  My husband's and my order was delivered on one plate.  When I expressed surprise that it was delivered in that manner I was told that my order was on one side of the plate and my husband's was on the other.  Only after I expressed my displeasure were we given separate plates.  My husband ordered a salad which they forgot to bring until we inquired about it.   Although I ordered six peri peri wings I was given five tough drummettes and one flat piece.  Normally you get three of each and they are all quite tender.  When I asked about this I was told that it depended on the cook.  Several staff members inquired if everything was alright and when I expressed my displeasure the response was always "I'm so sorry".  There was no genuine concern.  I will never eat at this Nando's again . It really does a disservice to the Nando brand.  I must add that after I wrote this review a young employee named Stevenson asked me if I enjoyed my meal.  When I told him about my dissatisfaction he told Lee Meija, the manager.  She genuinely apologized and reimbursed me  for my meal.  Stevenson also gave me a voucher for a free meal as well as a free appetizer.  I left feeling that my concerns were addressed and that corrective action was going to be taken so that nothing like this ever happened again.
